### Phase 9 — Admin Dashboard Negative Security Tests
### Run via VS Code REST Client or any HTTP client.
### Requires DB running (docker compose up -d).
### Requires one ADMIN user and one USER user.

### Variables (set these)
@adminToken = <ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN>
@userToken = <USER_JWT_TOKEN>
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### ==========================================
### 1. Unauthenticated admin API request fails
### ==========================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/health
// Expected: 401 { "error": "Authentication required." }

### ==========================================
### 2. USER role admin API request fails
### ==========================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/health
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
// Expected: 403 { "error": "Forbidden. Admin access required." }

### ==========================================
### 3. ADMIN request succeeds
### ==========================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/health
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
// Expected: 200 { "status": "healthy", "counts": { ... } }

### ==========================================
### 4. Invalid id rejected (memory delete)
### ==========================================
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/memories/nonexistent-id
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
// Expected: 404 { "error": "Memory not found." }

### ==========================================
### 5. Invalid id rejected (candidate delete)
### ==========================================
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/learning-candidates/nonexistent-id
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
// Expected: 404 { "error": "Learning candidate not found." }

### ==========================================
### 6. Admin API does not return passwordHash
### ==========================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
// Expected: 200 { "users": [...] }
// Verify: NO user object has "passwordHash" field

### ==========================================
### 7. Admin API does not return session tokens
### ==========================================
// Session tokens are in the Session model.
// No admin API reads the Session model. Verified by code review.

### ==========================================
### 8. Admin cannot set invalid role
### ==========================================
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{someUserId}}/role
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "role": "SUPER_ADMIN" }
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Role must be ADMIN or USER." }

### ==========================================
### 9. Admin cannot demote self if zero admins remain
### ==========================================
### Step 1: Get the admin user's ID from GET /api/admin/users
### Step 2: Try to demote that admin to USER
// PATCH /api/admin/users/{adminId}/role (as that admin)
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Cannot demote self. No other admin exists." }

### ==========================================
### 10. Client-side role spoofing does not work
### ==========================================
### The admin check is server-side (requireAdmin() in every route handler).
### Client role is not trusted — session.role from JWT is verified server-side.
### Verified by code review.

### ==========================================
### 11. Admin dashboard redirect for non-admin users
### ==========================================
### GET /dashboard/admin (as USER role)
### Expected: 302 redirect to /dashboard
### Implementation: session.user.role !== "ADMIN" → redirect("/dashboard")

### ==========================================
### 12. Unauthenticated GET /dashboard/admin redirects to login
### ==========================================
### GET /dashboard/admin (unauthenticated)
### Expected: 302 redirect to /login
